Police were called to Wardown Park in Luton at around 3.15pm to reports a teenager had been stabbed.  He has been taken to hospital with injuries that are thought to be life-threatening. The scene has been cordoned off by officers.  Bedfordshire Police tweeted: "We are currently at the scene of an incident in Wardown Park, Luton. "We were called at around 3.15pm to a report that teenager had been stabbed. "He has been taken to hospital with injuries currently believed to be life-threatening." The force is urging anyone with information to contact them via their website or on 101 quoting reference 288 of 28 February. 